WEBVTT

01:39.460 --> 01:40.460
Is anybody there?

01:42.590 --> 01:43.590
Jeanne.

01:46.890 --> 01:48.140
I'm happy to see you...

01:48.390 --> 01:51.140
but to keep coming here twice,
three times a day...

01:51.390 --> 01:52.390
I need to confess.

01:52.680 --> 01:54.270
You confessed this morning.

01:54.520 --> 01:56.190
I need to confess again.

01:56.980 --> 01:59.360
What terrible sin
have you committed...

01:59.610 --> 02:01.940
that can't wait till tomorrow?

02:02.190 --> 02:06.240
I saw a poor monk without shoes,
so I gave him some.

02:06.450 --> 02:08.699
There's no sin in charity, Jeanne.

02:09.449 --> 02:11.120
They weren't my shoes.

02:11.370 --> 02:13.790
- Whose were they?
- My father's.

02:14.290 --> 02:17.330
- I'm sure he'll forgive you.
- He already did.

02:17.580 --> 02:19.540
I want Jesus to forgive me too.

02:20.250 --> 02:23.300
If we asked forgiveness
all the time, we'd spend...

02:23.550 --> 02:25.090
our whole life in church.

02:25.340 --> 02:26.380
Is that bad?

02:26.630 --> 02:29.010
Well, no, but...

02:31.100 --> 02:32.310
Are you happy at home?

02:32.760 --> 02:34.270
Yes, very.

02:34.520 --> 02:36.680
Your mother?
Everything's fine with her?

02:37.190 --> 02:39.230
Yes, she's wonderful.

02:39.440 --> 02:42.360
And your sister, Catherine?
Is she still your best friend?

02:42.610 --> 02:44.360
My sister's just...

02:44.610 --> 02:46.360
She's wonderful.

02:46.610 --> 02:48.610
What about your other friends?

02:48.860 --> 02:51.160
You don't like playing with them?

02:51.410 --> 02:53.370
I play with them lots.

02:54.120 --> 02:57.330
Everything sounds wonderful.

02:57.660 --> 02:59.290
Yes, it is.

02:59.540 --> 03:01.920
Then why are you here so often?

03:03.500 --> 03:05.510
I feel safe here.

03:05.800 --> 03:08.010
It's where I can talk to him.

03:09.300 --> 03:10.470
Him?

03:11.390 --> 03:13.890
Well, I try to talk to him.

03:14.140 --> 03:17.180
But mostly he's the one
who does the talking.

03:18.060 --> 03:19.890
Who is this...

03:20.810 --> 03:21.940
"he"?

03:23.110 --> 03:24.650
He never says his name.

03:26.650 --> 03:30.110
What does he...

03:30.490 --> 03:31.990
look like?

03:38.120 --> 03:39.710
Beautiful.

03:44.790 --> 03:46.170
What does he say to you?

03:47.210 --> 03:48.670
He says...

03:54.930 --> 03:59.020
He says I must be good
and help everyone...

03:59.270 --> 04:01.810
and take care of myself.

04:03.100 --> 04:05.570
Do you think he's coming
from the sky?

04:06.980 --> 04:08.490
Perhaps.

04:10.030 --> 04:14.070
But wherever he's coming from,
I think you should listen to him.

04:14.320 --> 04:18.500
Because it sounds like
he's giving you very good advice.

04:26.290 --> 04:27.300
Amen.

04:44.020 --> 04:46.060
It's wonderful!

04:47.320 --> 04:48.940
It's wonderful.

06:05.980 --> 06:07.980
Jeanne...

06:11.900 --> 06:13.820
Jeanne...

07:32.230 --> 07:33.900
Jeanne...

10:13.020 --> 10:14.270
Mother!

10:15.730 --> 10:16.730
Mother!

10:20.980 --> 10:21.980
Catherine!

10:24.360 --> 10:25.740
Catherine!

10:34.660 --> 10:36.830
Are you all right?
Did they hurt you?

10:37.290 --> 10:38.670
No, I'm fine. Really.

10:39.670 --> 10:42.210
We looked for you.
The English are everywhere.

10:42.460 --> 10:44.300
I was in the church.

10:44.550 --> 10:47.930
I was talking to the priest.
Do you know what he said?

10:48.970 --> 10:51.300
Tell me later.
Quick, hide in here!

10:52.760 --> 10:55.350
- Where will you be?
- I'll be right here.

10:55.600 --> 10:57.230
I promise.

11:05.030 --> 11:06.400
That's what I call booty.

11:43.770 --> 11:44.980
Comrade.

12:01.000 --> 12:02.830
A woman with a sword.

12:05.090 --> 12:06.670
Look at this.

12:07.550 --> 12:10.510
Frenchmen are cowards,
they've left the women to fight.

12:11.130 --> 12:14.550
If that's God's will,
then so be it.

12:15.510 --> 12:16.930
Fine with me.

12:17.180 --> 12:18.430
I love women.

12:41.790 --> 12:45.790
Hold still, bitch. How can I do it
if you keep wriggling about?

13:37.550 --> 13:38.890
Your turn now.

14:12.090 --> 14:14.800
Preserve and bless the soul
of our dear departed.

14:15.180 --> 14:18.260
Keep us safe from fear and sin. Amen.

15:06.600 --> 15:07.600
Listen, Jeanne.

15:07.850 --> 15:12.150
Your aunt and uncle are taking you
to their house for a couple of weeks.

15:12.400 --> 15:14.980
Just to give us time
to rebuild things here.

15:23.410 --> 15:24.740
You understand?

16:34.810 --> 16:37.150
We give thanks for the food
you've given us.

16:37.400 --> 16:41.650
Teach us to love this land and save it
from those who seek to destroy it.

16:41.910 --> 16:43.410
Amen.

17:07.220 --> 17:09.270
So good night, then.

17:16.020 --> 17:17.569
What will happen to her?

17:17.900 --> 17:19.940
She'll be fine.

17:20.190 --> 17:24.859
She'll grow up, find a good man,
make him some children. Don't worry.

17:25.069 --> 17:29.790
She's been hurt, but she'll survive.
Tomorrow she'll be as right as rain.

17:29.990 --> 17:31.370
You'll see.

17:36.210 --> 17:38.090
I want to see a priest.

18:00.860 --> 18:02.360
Why did she have to die?

18:02.900 --> 18:05.110
Only God can answer that.

18:05.320 --> 18:08.740
I know Jesus says to love
your enemies, but I can't.

18:08.950 --> 18:12.950
I just want the English to burn
in Hell forever and ever!

18:13.790 --> 18:17.710
I realize your anger, Jeanne,
but we must learn to forgive.

18:17.960 --> 18:19.130
It's hard...

18:19.340 --> 18:22.880
but revenge will never
bring about peace.

18:23.130 --> 18:25.510
What will? And what
will bring her back?

18:25.720 --> 18:29.300
And why did she have to die
in the first place, instead of me?

18:29.510 --> 18:32.220
Why didn't He take my life
instead of hers?

18:32.430 --> 18:37.350
It was my fault! I was late!
She gave me her hiding place!

18:37.560 --> 18:39.480
Why did He save me?

18:39.690 --> 18:43.110
Calm down, Jeanne. Calm down.

18:45.360 --> 18:48.700
I don't pretend to know God's will...

18:48.910 --> 18:51.240
but one thing I am sure.

18:51.740 --> 18:55.410
The Lord always has a good reason.

18:56.250 --> 18:59.500
Perhaps He chose you because
He needs you for some...

19:00.080 --> 19:01.880
higher calling.

19:02.500 --> 19:07.220
As long as you answer that call,
your sister will not have died in vain.

19:09.470 --> 19:11.640
I don't want to wait for His call.

19:12.060 --> 19:13.640
Jeanne, be patient.

19:13.850 --> 19:15.680
I want to be with Him always.

19:15.930 --> 19:19.650
Soon you will be able
to take part in the Holy Mass.

19:19.900 --> 19:22.940
When you eat of His flesh
and drink of His blood...

19:23.150 --> 19:25.240
you will be at one with Him.

19:25.490 --> 19:28.780
I want to be at one with Him now.

19:35.450 --> 19:37.120
So what did he say?

19:37.410 --> 19:40.040
We must bring her to church
whenever she wants.

19:40.250 --> 19:43.630
Easy for him. He's not the one
that has to do the bringing.

19:43.840 --> 19:48.380
Come on, this is important.
We mustn't let her out of our sight.

19:49.260 --> 19:53.390
Don't worry. I will watch her
like my own shadow.

20:42.190 --> 20:45.520
I want to be at one with You now.

21:16.760 --> 21:19.140
A message for the dauphin of France.

21:28.440 --> 21:29.440
A message!

21:39.740 --> 21:42.290
Captain, a message for the dauphin.

21:42.540 --> 21:43.920
I'll take it.

21:51.210 --> 21:52.260
The dauphin!

22:08.150 --> 22:11.650
Louis. Shouldn't you
be learning your lessons?

22:11.860 --> 22:13.570
I don't want to.
I want to fight.

22:13.780 --> 22:17.320
You will. But for now, you must
at least learn to wipe your nose.

22:22.750 --> 22:24.080
A letter for His Majesty.

22:29.170 --> 22:32.590
Again from this girl calling
herself the Maiden of Lorraine.

22:32.800 --> 22:35.260
I can read for myself, you know.

22:35.510 --> 22:37.550
She says she's been sent by God.

22:37.800 --> 22:41.100
Charlatans. Pity there isn't
enough wood to burn them.

22:41.350 --> 22:42.770
She'll be here tomorrow.

22:42.970 --> 22:47.770
You can't see her. We don't even know
if she is from Lorraine.

22:47.980 --> 22:49.860
What difference does it make?

22:50.110 --> 22:53.150
If she's from Burgundy,
it might be a trap.

22:53.360 --> 22:56.450
Look. Signed "X."
What sort of a name is X?

22:56.650 --> 22:59.660
Must we assume a messenger of God
can't write her name?

22:59.870 --> 23:01.240
Trйmoille is correct.

23:01.450 --> 23:05.500
She says she hears voices.
She may be a sorceress, a witch.

23:05.750 --> 23:09.000
Regnault, you see witches everywhere.

23:09.210 --> 23:11.130
She's just a peasant.

23:11.340 --> 23:14.590
A peasant who cares about her king.

23:14.800 --> 23:18.800
All she wants is to see me crowned
and permission to fight for me.

23:19.010 --> 23:22.810
Not exactly. She wants you
to give her an army at your expense.

23:23.060 --> 23:26.180
Since your mother stole
all the gold in the treasury...

23:26.390 --> 23:28.440
I don't see how you can afford it.

23:28.650 --> 23:30.650
I can see her if I want to.

23:34.530 --> 23:38.150
The English control half of France.
What have I got to lose?

23:38.780 --> 23:39.990
The other half.

23:40.370 --> 23:42.410
You mustn't see her, Your Majesty.

23:42.620 --> 23:44.580
She may be an instrument of the Devil.

23:44.790 --> 23:46.500
Well, I think you should.

23:53.380 --> 23:54.880
Here's an amusing situation.

23:55.090 --> 23:58.680
I'd love to know why
my mother-in-law thinks one thing...

23:58.930 --> 24:01.760
and my two most loyal
and trusted advisers...

24:02.010 --> 24:04.470
think precisely the opposite.

24:05.060 --> 24:07.180
Because I care about you.

24:08.060 --> 24:09.270
Come here.

24:19.320 --> 24:22.490
Your happiness has always
been my first concern, Charles.

24:22.700 --> 24:24.660
Ever since you were a boy.

24:24.870 --> 24:26.620
I know you better
than your own mother.

24:26.830 --> 24:27.830
You think so?

24:29.580 --> 24:30.960
Yes.

24:31.580 --> 24:34.750
I know, for example, the sickness
that plagues your heart.

24:35.000 --> 24:38.050
I know how painful it is for you
to have loved a father...

24:38.260 --> 24:41.180
without ever knowing
if he was really yours.

24:43.640 --> 24:45.560
Do I know you enough?

24:48.220 --> 24:50.480
What has that got to do
with this maiden?

24:50.690 --> 24:54.860
Who better than a messenger from God
to give answers to your questions?

24:55.980 --> 24:57.820
You think she was sent from God?

24:58.690 --> 25:00.610
You're a fine judge of character.

25:00.820 --> 25:03.820
It will take you five minutes
to know if she's a fake.

25:04.990 --> 25:07.620
But if she's not...

25:09.870 --> 25:12.250
then she will give you
your answers...

25:14.420 --> 25:16.840
and place the crown on your head.

25:19.550 --> 25:23.130
With respect to my lady, it will
take more than a peasant girl...

25:23.340 --> 25:26.890
I'm not interested in what you think,
or even what I think.

25:27.100 --> 25:28.890
What simple people think matters.

25:29.100 --> 25:31.890
And simple people up
and down this country...

25:32.100 --> 25:34.810
are already talking about her.

25:35.480 --> 25:37.690
You know what simple people are like.

25:37.900 --> 25:41.030
Always ready to believe
any old prophecy.

25:44.860 --> 25:46.450
Like this one.

25:46.950 --> 25:50.040
About a virgin from Lorraine...

25:50.290 --> 25:52.080
saving France.

25:56.960 --> 25:58.550
And now...

25:59.840 --> 26:02.630
this girl comes along...

26:02.840 --> 26:04.590
from Lorraine...

26:05.800 --> 26:09.560
and suddenly there's a spark of hope
in their simple minds.

26:17.860 --> 26:19.980
You shouldn't disappoint them, Charles.

26:20.400 --> 26:22.530
If they believe in her...

26:23.450 --> 26:26.490
if she can put back
the fire in our army...

26:27.160 --> 26:29.870
then I believe in her too.

26:45.130 --> 26:47.340
Stop it, Louis! Stop!

26:50.100 --> 26:52.350
Louis, be quiet for once.

27:10.240 --> 27:14.450
- She's coming, Your Majesty.
- All right. Calm yourself.

27:15.040 --> 27:19.080
I urge you not to see this woman.
It reeks of a Burgundian trap.

27:19.330 --> 27:22.340
My astrologers assure me that
the timing is propitious.

27:22.550 --> 27:23.880
Leo with Virgo rising.

27:24.130 --> 27:27.220
Have you never noticed
on the astrological chart...

27:27.470 --> 27:29.720
that the virgin is next to the lion?

27:29.930 --> 27:32.180
Supposing she's an assassin?

27:34.680 --> 27:37.440
My dear Trйmoille,
I'm not even king yet.

27:37.690 --> 27:40.020
Who would want to assassinate me?

28:31.820 --> 28:34.330
She's arrived.
She's in the guards' room.

28:34.530 --> 28:35.790
Fine.

28:39.580 --> 28:43.080
I suppose I shall have
to make a decision.

28:52.340 --> 28:54.760
Why is life so complicated?

28:56.390 --> 28:59.560
Sometimes I really wish
I could be someone else.

29:01.520 --> 29:03.520
That's a good idea, sire.

29:07.230 --> 29:08.740
What do you mean?

29:09.030 --> 29:11.650
Let someone else pretend to be you.

29:11.950 --> 29:14.660
And see if she can find me.
A brilliant idea.

29:14.870 --> 29:17.740
If she's been sent by God,
she'll discover the trap.

29:17.950 --> 29:21.290
If she's an assassin,
she'll kill the wrong man.

29:28.340 --> 29:30.220
Please. Please!

29:30.720 --> 29:34.220
We're going to play a little game.

29:35.510 --> 29:40.060
Now, let us pretend
that my throne is empty.

29:40.270 --> 29:41.890
Just pretend.

29:42.980 --> 29:44.560
Who wants to be king?

29:48.860 --> 29:51.280
Now there's a heartwarming sight.

29:54.490 --> 29:56.070
Now, let us see.

29:56.320 --> 29:58.950
Which one of you could possibly pass...

29:59.160 --> 30:01.790
as the king of France?

30:02.620 --> 30:06.540
Alenзon, my noble duke,
my royal cousin...

30:06.750 --> 30:08.500
so fine, so brave, so rich.

30:08.880 --> 30:13.010
So very rich. So far-too-rich
to be the king of France.

30:13.260 --> 30:16.930
Everyone knows I'm the poorest man
in my kingdom.

30:20.140 --> 30:21.140
Gilles de Rais.

30:21.390 --> 30:23.230
Marshal of France.

30:23.730 --> 30:26.980
Formidable to men,
fascinating to women.

30:27.230 --> 30:28.860
Feared by all.

30:29.110 --> 30:33.190
You would be perfect
to sit on my throne.

30:33.400 --> 30:36.570
So perfect that you
might like it too much...

30:36.820 --> 30:40.910
and therefore disturb
my fragile peace of mind.

30:45.460 --> 30:46.540
La Hire.

30:47.380 --> 30:48.420
My angry captain.

30:48.670 --> 30:49.920
Bravest in France.

30:50.170 --> 30:54.420
Scarred by a dozen wars but with
the heart and stomach for a dozen more.

30:54.630 --> 30:56.090
You could pass for the king.

30:56.300 --> 30:57.550
Bloody right, I could.

30:57.760 --> 31:02.100
Except that no one with a tongue
like that could be king of France.

31:11.730 --> 31:16.070
Well, it looks like it shall
have to be me after all.

31:18.200 --> 31:19.620
Why not you?

31:19.910 --> 31:21.490
Jean d'Aulon.

31:23.450 --> 31:28.370
The only man who's poorer than I am,
therefore the only man I can trust.

31:30.080 --> 31:32.880
Dignified, honorable, wise.

31:33.090 --> 31:35.670
What more can we ask of a king?

31:40.930 --> 31:44.270
- I'm not sure...
- You're not ready to die for your king?

31:44.470 --> 31:45.600
- I am.
- Good.

31:45.810 --> 31:48.770
Until then, feel free to live
like a king. Bring her up.

31:59.200 --> 32:02.120
Sire, you know how bad I am
at this sort of game.

32:02.330 --> 32:04.040
Pretend it's not a game.

32:05.580 --> 32:07.160
Make way for the dauphin.

32:17.050 --> 32:19.050
- Mother?
- Not now.

33:12.400 --> 33:14.440
I have come to see the dauphin.

34:08.280 --> 34:09.280
Who are you?

34:10.500 --> 34:11.659
I'm...

34:13.159 --> 34:18.130
His most gracious Majesty,
Charles de Valois, Dauphin of France.

34:21.130 --> 34:22.130
Yes.

34:38.570 --> 34:40.860
I can see you are a good man.

34:41.730 --> 34:43.190
But you're not the dauphin.

34:47.699 --> 34:50.699
I'm sorry to insist,
but I must see the dauphin.

34:50.949 --> 34:53.909
We have no time to lose.
Where is he?

34:55.540 --> 34:56.920
He's here.

34:58.840 --> 35:00.670
Find him yourself.

35:26.990 --> 35:29.700
Now you'll see who'll pass for a king.

36:42.520 --> 36:45.650
There's no need to be afraid, sire.

36:48.240 --> 36:49.360
I'm not the king.

36:49.820 --> 36:54.280
I know you're not yet,
but you will be soon.

37:06.090 --> 37:07.210
Out.

37:11.470 --> 37:13.180
How did you know who I am?

37:13.390 --> 37:15.220
- Her voices.
- "That's him," they said.

37:15.430 --> 37:18.060
"The one in the corner
with the big nose."

37:24.650 --> 37:25.820
Back off!

37:30.820 --> 37:32.910
My gentle dauphin.

37:33.280 --> 37:34.740
Oh, my gentle dauphin.

37:42.250 --> 37:44.000
I have a message...

37:44.460 --> 37:47.090
from the King of Heaven...

37:47.550 --> 37:48.960
for you.

37:50.590 --> 37:52.800
You only.

38:02.190 --> 38:03.560
Follow me.

38:05.730 --> 38:06.940
Your Majesty, I plead...

38:07.150 --> 38:09.940
My dear loyal Trйmoille,
I know I can count on you...

38:10.190 --> 38:11.570
As always, Majesty.

38:11.780 --> 38:16.070
To ensure our privacy.
I need to talk to her alone.

38:21.830 --> 38:24.620
He needs to talk to her alone.

38:24.920 --> 38:26.080
Fine.

38:44.310 --> 38:45.940
I was about 10 years old.

38:46.810 --> 38:51.230
It was a beautiful spring day. I was
taking a shortcut through the forest...

38:51.440 --> 38:54.780
when a strange wind...

38:55.950 --> 38:57.570
began to blow.

39:05.920 --> 39:10.000
<i>It was such a strange sound,
almost like words...</i>

39:10.380 --> 39:12.170
calling me.

39:31.520 --> 39:33.230
The second time...

39:34.780 --> 39:36.700
was many years later.

39:37.240 --> 39:40.910
I was coming back from church
when suddenly...

39:41.120 --> 39:43.080
the same...

39:43.290 --> 39:46.250
violent wind.

39:52.050 --> 39:53.460
Then...

39:55.670 --> 39:57.430
<i>a shape...</i>

39:58.010 --> 39:59.300
<i>appeared...</i>

40:01.810 --> 40:04.220
<i>in the middle of the sky.</i>

40:04.470 --> 40:05.770
The shape...

40:09.810 --> 40:11.150
of a man.

40:25.540 --> 40:27.830
Everything was moving so fast.

40:28.040 --> 40:29.040
So fast.

40:31.670 --> 40:33.000
The wind, the clouds...

40:34.800 --> 40:37.510
I couldn't move.
I couldn't breathe.

40:39.720 --> 40:42.760
I was so frightened.

40:44.220 --> 40:45.390
He was...

40:47.020 --> 40:48.020
so...

40:51.310 --> 40:52.690
here.

41:03.030 --> 41:05.120
Then I knew that God had chosen me.

41:05.330 --> 41:09.830
But I did not understand what He
wanted me to do. What was my mission?

41:10.290 --> 41:12.500
What could I do to help my country?

41:12.710 --> 41:15.670
But how? I was nothing.
I was just a poor girl.

41:15.920 --> 41:20.880
I did not know anything
about making war or riding.

41:22.180 --> 41:24.390
So I decided to wait...

41:25.260 --> 41:27.560
and not speak of it to anybody.

41:27.770 --> 41:30.270
You did well. You did well.

41:30.480 --> 41:32.980
I didn't wait long.

41:34.400 --> 41:36.480
I was going to Mass...

41:37.320 --> 41:39.320
like I do every day...

41:40.320 --> 41:41.910
when the same...

41:42.410 --> 41:44.030
strange...

41:44.490 --> 41:45.660
wind...

42:14.520 --> 42:16.730
Everything was made clear.

42:19.110 --> 42:21.320
God had given me a message.

42:22.610 --> 42:24.860
A message to deliver.

42:30.790 --> 42:32.410
What was the message?

42:41.630 --> 42:43.010
He said...

42:44.050 --> 42:46.970
that I must save France
from her enemies...

42:47.550 --> 42:50.390
and bring her back
into the hands of God.

42:51.100 --> 42:53.810
And He told me that I...

42:54.020 --> 42:55.730
Jeanne...

42:56.400 --> 42:59.020
will lead you
to the altar at Reims...

43:01.570 --> 43:03.650
where you will be crowned...

43:05.820 --> 43:07.070
the king...

43:12.450 --> 43:14.500
of France.

43:37.900 --> 43:39.980
- Sire, are you?
- Fine. I'm fine.

43:42.110 --> 43:46.280
This is, in fact, Jean D'Aulon,
my loyal friend and finest archer.

43:46.490 --> 43:48.320
Jean, I put her in your care.

43:48.570 --> 43:52.200
Find her suitable lodgings
here in the castle...

43:52.410 --> 43:54.370
and guard her with your life.

43:54.580 --> 43:57.710
Sire, I won't need lodging
if we're to march on Orlйans.

43:57.920 --> 44:00.210
Orlйans has held out for six months.

44:00.460 --> 44:04.130
A few days more won't make
much difference. Take some rest.

44:12.220 --> 44:13.600
Put the bags here.

44:15.560 --> 44:19.850
Please accept my apologies for me
pretending to be the, you know...

44:20.810 --> 44:22.610
Could I have some water?

44:22.900 --> 44:23.900
Water...

44:23.980 --> 44:26.820
Yes, of course.
Would you get some water?

44:27.650 --> 44:29.240
- Anything else?
- A priest.

44:29.820 --> 44:30.820
Now?

44:30.870 --> 44:34.120
Yes. I didn't confess today.

44:35.290 --> 44:36.450
Right.

44:37.290 --> 44:39.370
Raymond, a priest.

44:39.620 --> 44:42.960
- Anything else?
- I shall also need a new warhorse...

44:43.170 --> 44:45.880
a sword, armour...

44:46.130 --> 44:48.590
and an artist to make
a banner for me.

44:48.800 --> 44:49.800
Now?

44:49.880 --> 44:51.590
Better today than tomorrow.

44:52.050 --> 44:54.760
This might take a little time...

44:55.600 --> 44:57.730
but let me see what I can do.

44:59.100 --> 45:01.940
I shall also need someone
who can read and write.

45:02.270 --> 45:07.030
I studied at the University of Paris
until the English invaded.

45:07.240 --> 45:09.780
- I thought you were an archer.
- Yes, I am.

45:10.320 --> 45:14.450
I'm an archer who can read and write.
Who do you want to write to?

45:15.080 --> 45:16.580
The king of England.

45:18.790 --> 45:22.130
I want to give him the chance
to leave in peace...

45:23.790 --> 45:25.710
before I get to Orlйans.

45:36.510 --> 45:40.350
The archbishop and I have begun
negotiations with the Burgundians.

45:40.560 --> 45:42.150
If we bring them to our side...

45:42.400 --> 45:45.650
Negotiate, by all means,
but from a position of strength.

45:45.860 --> 45:50.700
If the English take Orlйans,
there'll be nothing left to negotiate.

45:50.900 --> 45:53.410
My lady, it will be
the height of folly...

45:53.620 --> 45:57.950
to let this child lead our army
in the king's name...

45:58.160 --> 46:00.540
without verifying her true motives.

46:00.790 --> 46:02.620
My lord Trйmoille is right.

46:02.870 --> 46:07.130
We must be absolutely certain that
she's not an instrument of the devil.

46:07.340 --> 46:11.550
How can anyone be absolutely
certain about anything?

46:13.010 --> 46:16.550
Sometimes our intuitions
are our best counsellors.

46:16.810 --> 46:21.180
We must listen to Mother Holy Church
before we listen to our intuitions.

46:26.900 --> 46:27.900
Wait.

46:29.860 --> 46:31.990
She claims to be a virgin.

46:33.110 --> 46:35.740
Well, that's something we can examine...

46:35.950 --> 46:39.040
and be absolutely certain about.

46:55.970 --> 46:57.640
Let's find out.

49:31.000 --> 49:32.580
What if she's not?

49:33.040 --> 49:37.170
If she's not, I'll kill her myself.

49:47.270 --> 49:50.940
There is no sign of corruption
or violation.

49:51.310 --> 49:53.060
She is intact.

49:57.320 --> 50:00.700
And what exactly was
this vision wearing?

50:01.490 --> 50:03.030
I don't remember.

50:03.240 --> 50:05.870
This vision, did it give you anything?

50:06.280 --> 50:08.830
An object? A ring or a rosary...

50:09.040 --> 50:12.460
or anything by which we can
verify your claim?

50:12.670 --> 50:14.290
He gave me good advice.

50:14.500 --> 50:17.840
As a child, did you have
any sort of military experience?

50:18.090 --> 50:19.090
No.

50:19.460 --> 50:21.970
Practice in the skills
of swordsmanship?

50:22.550 --> 50:25.050
No. But I'm good with a stick.

50:29.850 --> 50:31.890
Do you know what a Dijon culverin is?

50:33.060 --> 50:34.060
No.

50:34.100 --> 50:35.520
It's an item of artillery.

50:35.770 --> 50:39.980
How can you raise the siege of Orlйans
if you're ignorant about artillery?

50:40.190 --> 50:42.320
The road to Orlйans is long.

50:42.570 --> 50:47.120
And I have good captains with me.
I will learn fast, believe me.

50:47.330 --> 50:49.160
We'd like to believe you...

50:49.490 --> 50:54.420
but we feel that if God wanted us to
believe you, He'd have sent a sign...

50:55.000 --> 50:56.040
with you.

50:56.250 --> 51:00.090
So can you do something?

51:02.170 --> 51:04.180
Show us something?

51:05.930 --> 51:11.060
A sign to prove that you
are sent by God?

51:12.810 --> 51:16.480
I did not come here to perform tricks.

51:19.190 --> 51:21.820
You are all much cleverer than I am.

51:22.740 --> 51:27.120
Me, I don't know "A" from "B."
But this much I do know:

51:28.240 --> 51:32.580
That while the people of France
lie bleeding...

51:32.790 --> 51:36.710
you sit around in your fine clothes
trying to deceive me...

51:36.920 --> 51:39.840
when you're only
deceiving yourselves.

51:40.750 --> 51:42.880
You say you are men of God...

51:43.130 --> 51:47.680
yet you do not see His hand
in having guided me...

51:48.010 --> 51:52.970
through 500 leagues of enemy country
to bring you His help.

51:53.770 --> 51:55.810
Is that not proof enough?

52:01.570 --> 52:03.940
Do you still need more signs?

52:10.120 --> 52:11.830
Give me an army.

52:14.410 --> 52:16.540
Take me to Orlйans...

52:20.670 --> 52:23.460
and there you'll see the sign
that I was sent to make.

52:53.620 --> 52:55.160
- Dunois.
- What?

52:55.370 --> 52:58.250
A big one. Straight at us.

53:01.040 --> 53:02.040
What side?

53:02.170 --> 53:03.340
Window side.

53:17.850 --> 53:19.350
Dunois!

53:19.560 --> 53:20.560
What?

53:22.270 --> 53:23.400
Wonderful news.

53:23.610 --> 53:27.490
Finally, he is sending her to us.
Thanks be to God. We're saved.

53:27.740 --> 53:29.240
It's wonderful.

53:29.450 --> 53:32.280
Calm yourself, Xaintrailles.
Who has done what?

53:32.490 --> 53:34.530
The dauphin.
He's sending us food...

53:34.740 --> 53:37.910
and an army led by Jeanne,
the Maiden from Lorraine.

53:38.160 --> 53:39.750
Isn't it wonderful?

53:40.960 --> 53:43.290
Yes. It's a miracle.

53:46.960 --> 53:49.760
I can't believe they are
sending a woman.

53:51.130 --> 53:53.720
I wonder what colour dress
she'll be wearing.

53:55.260 --> 53:56.260
Blue.

53:57.560 --> 54:00.600
With a blue ribbon in her hair
to tie up Talbot.

54:02.850 --> 54:05.480
Anyone know if she knows
how to ride a horse?

54:07.030 --> 54:08.030
She knows.

54:22.080 --> 54:23.540
Were you sent by Lord Dunois?

54:23.750 --> 54:25.840
Yes, they were.

54:26.090 --> 54:28.590
- Where are the English?
- Everywhere. The food?

54:28.800 --> 54:31.220
It's coming. I rode on ahead.

54:31.470 --> 54:34.430
I have a message for the captain
of the English army.

54:34.640 --> 54:35.970
- He is Talbot.
- I know.

54:36.180 --> 54:39.720
- Can you take me to him?
- He's on the other side of the river.

54:39.970 --> 54:43.230
So why was I brought
to this side of the river?

54:44.730 --> 54:46.060
Hey, my friend!

54:46.940 --> 54:48.610
Good to see your damn face.

54:48.860 --> 54:50.690
La Hire, don't swear.

54:50.940 --> 54:56.070
Sorry. Let me introduce the king's
half-brother, the dogged Lord Dunois.

54:57.700 --> 55:01.040
Then will you show me to
the other side of the river?

55:01.330 --> 55:02.370
Wait.

55:04.000 --> 55:05.040
Wait!

55:07.040 --> 55:10.170
Fine! Go now if you want!
But not with me!

55:10.380 --> 55:13.630
You may have a duty to God,
but I have a duty to my people.

55:13.880 --> 55:15.090
They are starving.

55:16.550 --> 55:19.140
I'm going to take the food
to the city.

55:19.390 --> 55:22.560
If you can calm down and let me
accompany you to Orlйans...

55:22.810 --> 55:25.520
it will be my honour
to welcome you.

56:23.910 --> 56:25.960
Jesus Christ.

56:26.540 --> 56:28.540
The goddamn English will pay for this.

56:28.750 --> 56:33.090
Yes, they will. And so will you
if you don't stop swearing.

56:51.020 --> 56:54.030
I'm happy to welcome you
in my tavern. Come on in.

56:58.320 --> 57:00.950
La Hire, Gilles,
let me show you something.

57:09.330 --> 57:13.040
Tourelles are around here.
The river crosses there.

57:17.340 --> 57:18.420
Calm down.

57:18.630 --> 57:20.930
Don't blame them.
They've been hearing...

57:21.140 --> 57:23.850
- about you for weeks.
- There's nothing to hear!

57:24.640 --> 57:27.060
And why? Because
I haven't done anything.

57:27.270 --> 57:30.730
Why haven't I done anything?
Because none of you will listen!

57:36.610 --> 57:38.530
Why don't you join us?

57:39.570 --> 57:41.200
We're discussing the campaign.

57:42.780 --> 57:43.780
I'm sorry.

57:44.660 --> 57:49.160
Talbot has spread his forces
between these forts up here.

57:49.460 --> 57:53.590
But in the last few days some troops
have been deployed to this fort.

57:54.340 --> 57:55.840
What's this pile here?

57:56.340 --> 57:58.920
The Tourelles.
The English planned to attack...

57:59.130 --> 58:01.300
from there, but
we broke the bridge...

58:01.550 --> 58:02.590
I did.

58:04.470 --> 58:06.470
Which should keep them
quiet for a while.

58:07.140 --> 58:10.060
Now, my hunch is, the attack...

58:10.270 --> 58:12.060
will come from St. Loup.

58:12.560 --> 58:15.400
And what does Jeanne think?

58:15.730 --> 58:19.150
I don't think. I leave that to God.

58:19.400 --> 58:22.320
I'm nothing in all this.
I'm just the messenger.

58:22.570 --> 58:23.620
So?

58:24.990 --> 58:25.990
The message?

58:26.700 --> 58:31.830
We give the English a last chance
to go home in peace.

58:32.170 --> 58:33.170
If they refuse?

58:33.630 --> 58:35.460
If they refuse...

58:37.710 --> 58:39.630
we recross the river...

58:40.970 --> 58:43.180
and attack here...

58:44.510 --> 58:45.890
at the Tourelles.

58:46.760 --> 58:49.100
But the Tourelles
is virtually impregnable.

58:49.310 --> 58:53.190
If we're on the other side of
the river attacking the Tourelles...

58:53.440 --> 58:56.730
what's to stop Talbot attacking
the city from the north?

58:57.070 --> 58:58.070
God.

58:58.400 --> 59:00.780
God! Why, of course.

59:01.400 --> 59:02.780
We'd forgotten about Him.

59:07.120 --> 59:09.660
I feel a great sorrow for you.

59:10.870 --> 59:14.460
You're laughing now, but by tomorrow
night some of you will be dead.

59:14.710 --> 59:18.460
We can't just attack the Tourelles.
It's a very complicated matter.

59:18.670 --> 59:20.960
What's so complicated about it?

59:21.210 --> 59:25.680
All you have to do is what you're told.
What could be simpler than that?

59:26.090 --> 59:29.470
I am the drum on which God
is beating out His message.

59:29.680 --> 59:32.480
He's beating it so hard
it's bursting my ears!

59:33.180 --> 59:34.270
You have to understand.

59:34.520 --> 59:39.150
It's not easy, I mean, for our pride,
to suddenly be usurped by...

59:43.610 --> 59:45.950
Well, with all due respect...

59:48.490 --> 59:49.620
by a girl.

59:54.370 --> 59:55.960
So that's it.

59:57.170 --> 01:00:00.130
To you, I'm just...

01:00:00.750 --> 01:00:01.840
a girl.

01:00:02.920 --> 01:00:07.720
Put yourself in my shoes for a moment.
How would you feel if you were me?

01:00:08.220 --> 01:00:10.140
Knowing what I know...

01:00:10.930 --> 01:00:13.930
enormous gratitude.

01:00:18.350 --> 01:00:20.020
One hell of a girl, huh?

01:00:26.240 --> 01:00:27.860
I warned you.

01:00:32.120 --> 01:00:35.960
I do love her when her fire
gets well and truly stoked.

01:00:36.500 --> 01:00:37.870
Me too.

01:00:39.630 --> 01:00:42.130
Hello, my friends!

01:00:43.210 --> 01:00:44.630
Quite a journey.

01:00:45.260 --> 01:00:46.840
But we made it.

01:00:48.260 --> 01:00:49.970
Together again.
Let's have some fun.

01:00:54.270 --> 01:00:57.020
Fine. I shall look like a man.

01:01:03.780 --> 01:01:04.780
Stop it!

01:01:05.150 --> 01:01:07.740
How dare you stop me
from doing God's will!

01:01:07.950 --> 01:01:09.200
He didn't say to cut your hair!

01:01:09.610 --> 01:01:12.080
How dare you tell me
what God tells me to do!

01:01:12.280 --> 01:01:15.370
Whatever! But since He's not
going to cut it Himself...

01:01:15.620 --> 01:01:18.120
at least let someone
cut it properly!

01:01:19.330 --> 01:01:23.590
Raymond, bring the scissors.
Louis, fetch the mirror.

01:01:27.470 --> 01:01:31.050
Jeanne, stop getting so angry
about everything. Calm down.

01:01:31.260 --> 01:01:34.510
I am calm! It's God that's angry.

01:01:35.010 --> 01:01:37.100
I need to send a letter. Now.

01:01:37.770 --> 01:01:38.770
Fine.

01:01:39.980 --> 01:01:41.810
<i>To you, Henry, king of England...</i>

01:01:42.060 --> 01:01:45.940
<i>and you, Duke of Bedford,
who call yourself regent of France...</i>

01:01:46.190 --> 01:01:49.570
<i>obey the King of Heaven
and abandon your siege.</i>

01:01:49.820 --> 01:01:54.950
<i>Give back the keys to the towns you've
taken and go back home to your island.</i>

01:01:55.240 --> 01:01:58.830
<i>To you, Lord Talbot, I beg you
as humbly as I can beg you...</i>

01:01:59.080 --> 01:02:03.840
<i>save the lives of your soldiers,
do not bring about your own destruction.</i>

01:02:04.090 --> 01:02:07.710
<i>Surrender to me, Jeanne the Maiden,
who is sent here by God.</i>

01:02:11.260 --> 01:02:12.550
Message!

01:02:13.800 --> 01:02:17.100
<i>If you do not leave,
we shall raise a battle cry...</i>

01:02:17.310 --> 01:02:20.390
<i>as there has not been heard
in France for 1000 years.</i>

01:02:29.030 --> 01:02:31.320
Sire, message.

01:02:31.910 --> 01:02:34.410
<i>This is the third and last time
I will write.</i>

01:02:34.620 --> 01:02:37.870
<i>If you are still here at noon,
you will hear from me...</i>

01:02:38.080 --> 01:02:39.790
<i>to your great destruction.</i>

01:02:40.040 --> 01:02:42.580
<i>Please give me your answer speedily.</i>

01:02:43.630 --> 01:02:45.920
Go fuck yourself!

01:02:48.380 --> 01:02:50.130
What did they say?

01:02:51.220 --> 01:02:53.680
They said they'll think about it.

01:02:55.140 --> 01:02:56.140
Good.

01:02:57.010 --> 01:02:59.640
But I don't think
they'll leave tomorrow.

01:03:03.850 --> 01:03:06.400
I can't wait for tomorrow.

01:03:33.930 --> 01:03:36.010
French blood is spilling.

01:03:40.010 --> 01:03:41.180
Wake up!

01:03:42.600 --> 01:03:43.600
Hurry!

01:03:45.650 --> 01:03:47.520
They've started without me.

01:03:54.030 --> 01:03:57.200
There's a battle to fight
and a war to be won.

01:04:01.200 --> 01:04:02.200
Damn!

01:04:06.370 --> 01:04:08.040
Sound the retreat!

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:11.050
My banner. My banner!

01:04:11.250 --> 01:04:12.460
My banner!

01:04:19.350 --> 01:04:20.810
Open the gate!

01:04:32.480 --> 01:04:35.860
What happened?
Who gave the order to attack?

01:04:36.110 --> 01:04:38.240
God knows. It was a bad idea.

01:04:38.620 --> 01:04:40.240
Where are the priests?

01:04:40.450 --> 01:04:43.700
We didn't take them.
We wanted to make a surprise attack.

01:04:44.160 --> 01:04:46.870
Dunois, you gave the order to attack?

01:04:47.960 --> 01:04:48.960
Answer me!

01:04:49.130 --> 01:04:51.710
- Can we discuss this later?
- Sooner is better.

01:04:55.760 --> 01:04:56.760
Wait!

01:04:56.800 --> 01:04:58.010
You'll be killed!

01:05:10.520 --> 01:05:12.070
Follow me!

01:05:12.360 --> 01:05:14.360
I will give you victory!

01:05:21.780 --> 01:05:22.780
Close it!

01:05:22.830 --> 01:05:24.580
Close the drawbridge!

01:05:47.390 --> 01:05:49.140
To the drawbridge!

01:05:49.350 --> 01:05:51.150
To the drawbridge!

01:05:53.150 --> 01:05:54.150
What's she doing?

01:05:54.520 --> 01:05:55.780
To the drawbridge!

01:05:55.980 --> 01:05:58.240
- The drawbridge is closed.
- Not for long!

01:06:07.040 --> 01:06:08.120
Let's go!

01:07:38.710 --> 01:07:40.170
That's mine!

01:07:50.390 --> 01:07:53.730
It's a great victory, Jeanne.
Your victory.

01:07:54.020 --> 01:07:58.730
We must pursue the English to Talbot's
camp, unless you have another idea.

01:07:58.940 --> 01:08:03.490
First, we find the biggest army we can.
Then we return to Orlйans.

01:08:03.700 --> 01:08:06.530
- The bridge is down.
- The English are rebuilding it.

01:08:07.490 --> 01:08:08.530
How do you know?

01:08:08.830 --> 01:08:12.870
You have been with your counsel,
and I have been with mine.

01:08:24.420 --> 01:08:26.300
Come on, come on! Hurry up.

01:08:49.029 --> 01:08:50.580
Be careful with my baby.

01:09:21.310 --> 01:09:22.979
That's the Tourelles.

01:09:23.399 --> 01:09:24.529
Wonderful.

01:09:24.729 --> 01:09:25.729
Captain!

01:09:32.120 --> 01:09:35.040
The froggy whore's coming
to pay us a visit.

01:09:35.250 --> 01:09:36.910
I'd better tell Glasdale.

01:09:42.170 --> 01:09:43.800
Put the horses over there.

01:09:49.550 --> 01:09:52.260
Fathers, please bless them.

01:09:52.470 --> 01:09:54.970
- Please, bless them all.
- We will.

01:10:10.570 --> 01:10:13.070
Let's plan this attack more carefully.

01:10:13.320 --> 01:10:14.910
Good idea.

01:10:19.710 --> 01:10:20.790
Sire.

01:10:22.880 --> 01:10:25.590
We've got visitors.

01:10:45.980 --> 01:10:46.980
Glasdale!

01:10:49.070 --> 01:10:50.450
Do you hear me?

01:10:51.610 --> 01:10:53.740
You, who call me a whore!

01:10:54.160 --> 01:10:57.490
I feel pity for you,
for your soul...

01:10:57.700 --> 01:10:59.620
and for the souls of your men!

01:11:00.370 --> 01:11:04.500
Yield! Yield now
to the King of Heaven!

01:11:05.880 --> 01:11:07.340
Or go back to your island!

01:11:07.750 --> 01:11:10.880
And you, go back to your pigsty!

01:11:17.720 --> 01:11:19.350
Man the walls.

01:11:40.700 --> 01:11:42.040
This morning...

01:11:43.500 --> 01:11:46.040
God gave us a great victory.

01:11:48.590 --> 01:11:53.090
But it is nothing compared to what
He is ready to give us now.

01:11:54.130 --> 01:11:57.100
I know you are all tired and hungry...

01:11:57.510 --> 01:11:59.390
but I swear to you...

01:11:59.890 --> 01:12:04.440
even if the English were hanging
from the clouds by their fingertips...

01:12:04.640 --> 01:12:07.150
we'd pull them down before nightfall.

01:12:09.690 --> 01:12:10.690
Now...

01:12:11.230 --> 01:12:13.280
let all those who love me...

01:12:16.070 --> 01:12:17.070
follow me!

01:12:24.830 --> 01:12:25.830
Follow me!

01:12:36.180 --> 01:12:37.720
You were saying?

01:12:44.430 --> 01:12:45.850
Come on!

01:12:49.230 --> 01:12:51.610
- I go right.
- I go left!

01:12:57.360 --> 01:12:58.570
Come on!

