Yes, my lady.

01:45:36.740 --> 01:45:41.790
True kings of France must be anointed
in Reims, with the holy oil of Clovis.

01:45:53.470 --> 01:45:57.510
- Your Grace! There can be no anointing.
- What are you talking about?

01:45:57.720 --> 01:46:00.100
The holy oil of Clovis, it's all gone!

01:46:00.310 --> 01:46:01.640
But that's impossible.

01:46:01.850 --> 01:46:05.560
It's a magic oil. Miraculous oil.
It can never be exhausted.

01:46:05.810 --> 01:46:07.770
- Look for yourself.
- Problem?

01:46:08.770 --> 01:46:09.810
I don't understand.

01:46:10.020 --> 01:46:12.980
The oil of Clovis, it was
full the last time I saw it.

01:46:13.190 --> 01:46:14.360
And when was that?

01:46:14.610 --> 01:46:16.610
The coronation of King Charles VI.

01:46:16.860 --> 01:46:20.410
Thirty years ago?
Does it surprise you it's gone?

01:46:20.660 --> 01:46:24.500
But you don't understand.
It's no ordinary oil.

01:46:24.750 --> 01:46:26.830
It's a miraculous oil.

01:46:27.210 --> 01:46:29.830
It was brought
by a dove from Heaven...

01:46:30.210 --> 01:46:33.380
to crown King Clovis
in this very cathedral.

01:46:34.840 --> 01:46:36.050
What are you doing?

01:46:36.260 --> 01:46:38.300
Performing a miracle.

01:47:57.550 --> 01:48:01.760
With this sacred oil, blessed by
the hand of God the Father Almighty...

01:48:02.010 --> 01:48:04.180
we do anoint thee, Charles Valois...

01:48:04.430 --> 01:48:09.560
to be sovereign lord and king
of this great kingdom of France...

01:48:09.850 --> 01:48:14.190
charging that ye shall defend
the faith of our Mother Holy Church...

01:48:14.440 --> 01:48:17.440
as long as ye shall live.

01:48:18.900 --> 01:48:20.280
Amen.

01:48:54.650 --> 01:48:55.980
Long live the king!

01:49:14.870 --> 01:49:17.460
- Jeanne, are you all right?
- I'm fine.

01:49:20.210 --> 01:49:21.800
Why are you staring at me?

01:49:22.010 --> 01:49:23.680
Because you have an arrow in your leg.

01:49:29.390 --> 01:49:30.970
So there is.

01:49:32.680 --> 01:49:34.770
But that doesn't stop you
from climbing!

01:49:36.060 --> 01:49:37.520
Go, climb! Go!

01:49:41.990 --> 01:49:42.990
Raymond!

01:49:45.320 --> 01:49:46.740
Take this arrow out.

01:49:52.040 --> 01:49:53.040
Look out!

01:49:55.370 --> 01:49:56.370
Be careful!

01:49:56.580 --> 01:49:58.540
Jeanne, the men are exhausted.

01:49:58.750 --> 01:50:01.460
I know, but so is the enemy.
Paris is ours.

01:50:01.710 --> 01:50:03.550
Jeanne, we're not enough.

01:50:03.800 --> 01:50:06.510
So bring up the reinforcements.

01:50:06.720 --> 01:50:08.850
Reinforcements? Where?

01:50:09.640 --> 01:50:11.180
Right behind us.

01:50:11.720 --> 01:50:14.430
Dunois with another 10,000 men.

01:50:14.640 --> 01:50:18.100
- Jeanne, look behind you!
- Never look behind. Only ahead!

01:50:19.860 --> 01:50:22.070
Do you know how to count?

01:50:25.700 --> 01:50:29.450
Of course I do! So, bring them up!

01:50:31.660 --> 01:50:35.790
Jeanne, that is not
10,000 reinforcements!

01:50:36.000 --> 01:50:40.880
That is 100 very loyal
but very tired soldiers!

01:50:43.510 --> 01:50:47.130
But where's Dunois? And where
are the men the king promised me?

01:50:47.380 --> 01:50:50.640
He never sent them!
Don't you understand?

01:50:51.260 --> 01:50:53.350
He doesn't want this war anymore.

01:50:53.560 --> 01:50:56.480
He has his crown now.
That's all he ever wanted.

01:50:57.390 --> 01:51:00.400
But my voices, they promised me.

01:51:00.610 --> 01:51:03.230
To hell with your voices!

01:51:06.440 --> 01:51:08.610
It's time to face facts!

01:51:11.160 --> 01:51:13.370
We have nothing to do here!

01:51:14.240 --> 01:51:15.580
None of us.

01:51:18.250 --> 01:51:19.620
Not even you.

01:51:25.340 --> 01:51:27.590
You don't believe in me anymore?

01:51:27.800 --> 01:51:30.510
Jeanne, of course
we still believe in you.

01:51:30.930 --> 01:51:34.680
If it were up to me, I'd chase
every Englishman into the ocean.

01:51:35.270 --> 01:51:37.480
But it's not up to us anymore.

01:51:37.850 --> 01:51:39.480
It's up to the king.

01:51:51.950 --> 01:51:53.700
You should go home, Jeanne.

01:52:08.550 --> 01:52:12.640
We cannot possibly afford to pay
for the size of army she's demanding.

01:52:12.890 --> 01:52:13.890
The girl is crazy.

01:52:16.100 --> 01:52:18.020
Orlйans was a miracle.

01:52:18.220 --> 01:52:21.730
But we can't wait for a miracle
when we build a future for France!

01:52:24.400 --> 01:52:26.780
Paris was a disaster.

01:52:27.610 --> 01:52:29.110
God wasn't with her then.

01:52:29.320 --> 01:52:32.240
If God deserts her,
what do you think we should do?

01:52:44.250 --> 01:52:48.050
Why did you betray me?
All I needed was a few hundred men.

01:52:48.920 --> 01:52:52.010
- Why did you take the army you gave me?
- Gave you?

01:52:52.880 --> 01:52:54.640
I wouldn't put it that way.

01:52:54.840 --> 01:52:56.140
How would you put it?

01:53:01.680 --> 01:53:06.690
We are, of course, enormously
grateful for your past efforts...

01:53:07.730 --> 01:53:09.530
but now your task is done.

01:53:09.820 --> 01:53:12.280
Now is the time for negotiation.

01:53:12.490 --> 01:53:14.610
Peace will only be got
at the end of a lance.

01:53:15.200 --> 01:53:18.870
Why are you so bloodthirsty?
Do you enjoy it?

01:53:20.540 --> 01:53:21.540
No.

01:53:21.580 --> 01:53:24.120
Diplomacy is far more civilized...

01:53:24.420 --> 01:53:27.290
far safer and far cheaper.

01:53:35.220 --> 01:53:39.760
I have letters here from towns under
siege, where people are starving...

01:53:40.010 --> 01:53:42.520
begging God on their knees
to help them.

01:53:42.730 --> 01:53:46.440
I'm here to answer their prayers.
And you want to stop me?

01:53:48.820 --> 01:53:52.240
France does not belong
to you, Charles.

01:53:52.440 --> 01:53:54.200
She belongs to God.

01:54:05.370 --> 01:54:08.330
If only she would just go home.

01:54:27.810 --> 01:54:29.610
What am I supposed to do now?

01:54:30.940 --> 01:54:32.440
What do your voices say?

01:54:32.650 --> 01:54:36.570
They haven't spoken to me in weeks.
Not since the coronation.

01:54:36.780 --> 01:54:38.660
No signs. Nothing.

01:54:40.280 --> 01:54:42.740
Maybe their silence is a sign.

01:54:43.580 --> 01:54:45.080
Maybe a sign to go home.

01:54:45.290 --> 01:54:49.210
It's not time yet.
My mission isn't over yet.

01:54:50.710 --> 01:54:52.960
There's still so much I have to do.

01:54:54.630 --> 01:54:56.220
How do you know that these...

01:54:56.510 --> 01:54:59.760
these voices aren't
just really you?

01:55:01.140 --> 01:55:02.970
Well, they are me.

01:55:03.600 --> 01:55:05.480
That's how God speaks to me.

01:55:07.520 --> 01:55:10.810
Even you could hear them
if you listened hard enough.

01:55:12.650 --> 01:55:14.570
You make it sound so simple.

01:55:16.280 --> 01:55:18.530
So even you don't
believe in me anymore.

01:55:19.450 --> 01:55:23.450
Jeanne, I believe in you
more than anyone.

01:55:23.910 --> 01:55:25.500
I just wish I could...

01:55:28.080 --> 01:55:29.370
help you.

01:55:29.580 --> 01:55:32.340
There is one thing you can do
to help me.

01:55:32.540 --> 01:55:33.550
Tell me.

01:55:33.750 --> 01:55:36.920
Tell the king to give back
the army that he gave me.

01:55:46.850 --> 01:55:49.230
We have to stop her, Your Majesty.

01:55:49.440 --> 01:55:52.560
If she raises an army
and attacks the Burgundians...

01:55:52.770 --> 01:55:56.150
months of negotiations
will have been in vain.

01:55:57.070 --> 01:55:59.240
Jeanne has done so much for us.

01:55:59.450 --> 01:56:02.870
I assure you, the maid has
no greater admirer than myself.

01:56:03.070 --> 01:56:04.740
But whatever we feel...

01:56:04.950 --> 01:56:08.460
we cannot allow her to conduct
her own private war.

01:56:08.870 --> 01:56:12.630
For the sake of the kingdom,
you must stop her going to Compiиgne.

01:56:12.880 --> 01:56:14.670
I can't stop her.

01:56:15.380 --> 01:56:20.300
Well, if you don't, I'm sure the
Burgundians would be happy to oblige.

01:56:20.630 --> 01:56:22.840
If they capture her at Compiиgne...

01:56:23.050 --> 01:56:25.390
No one can blame us.

01:56:29.890 --> 01:56:32.600
But it could sound like we betrayed her.

01:56:32.810 --> 01:56:34.520
- No, never.
- Good heavens, no!

01:56:34.770 --> 01:56:36.650
Don't worry, Charles.

01:56:39.190 --> 01:56:43.530
If God is still with her,
she will be victorious.

01:56:44.070 --> 01:56:45.830
But her army's so much smaller.

01:56:46.030 --> 01:56:48.870
Then her faith will have to be bigger.

01:57:03.380 --> 01:57:07.220
- Open this gate immediately.
- I can't risk the safety of my town.

01:57:10.560 --> 01:57:11.560
Take my banner!

01:58:09.240 --> 01:58:10.410
My Lord.

01:58:12.830 --> 01:58:13.830
My Lord.

01:58:38.900 --> 01:58:40.440
I can't believe it.

01:58:40.650 --> 01:58:45.490
Your romantic vision of death with
all that grass growing everywhere.

01:58:45.700 --> 01:58:48.200
I must admit you have
a big imagination.

01:58:48.910 --> 01:58:50.990
But maybe not big enough.

01:58:51.410 --> 01:58:53.450
Death is much more...

01:58:54.330 --> 01:58:55.330
simple.

01:58:58.500 --> 01:59:02.170
After a few months,
it gets more interesting.

01:59:05.010 --> 01:59:08.890
Then after a year,
it finally becomes...

01:59:10.890 --> 01:59:12.510
romantic.

01:59:17.890 --> 01:59:19.150
Who are you?

01:59:19.770 --> 01:59:21.650
You don't like my face?

01:59:22.230 --> 01:59:24.280
Maybe you'd prefer this one.

01:59:28.280 --> 01:59:29.860
Too young, maybe.

01:59:30.070 --> 01:59:31.830
How about this one?

01:59:34.740 --> 01:59:35.740
Better, no?

01:59:37.830 --> 01:59:39.500
But incomplete.

01:59:44.800 --> 01:59:47.760
Get thee behind me, Satan.

01:59:47.970 --> 01:59:53.010
Who are you to even think you can know
the difference between good and evil?

01:59:54.680 --> 01:59:56.020
Are you God?

02:00:00.440 --> 02:00:02.480
I'm just a messenger.

02:00:03.230 --> 02:00:04.440
He needs me.

02:00:04.650 --> 02:00:08.450
How can you imagine that God,
the creator of Heaven and Earth...

02:00:08.650 --> 02:00:10.610
the source of all life...

02:00:10.820 --> 02:00:14.580
could possibly need you?

02:00:16.450 --> 02:00:17.450
I don't know.

02:00:17.540 --> 02:00:20.370
You don't think He can
deliver His own messages?

02:00:21.290 --> 02:00:23.840
What do you want from me?

02:00:24.040 --> 02:00:26.250
Nothing. I'm here to set you free.

02:00:28.800 --> 02:00:30.840
I said smile. You have visitors.

02:00:31.090 --> 02:00:33.430
The Duke of Burgundy.

02:00:45.060 --> 02:00:47.230
So here's the famous Jeanne...

02:00:47.980 --> 02:00:51.070
saviour of Orlйans,
terror of the English.

02:00:51.400 --> 02:00:54.950
My king will pay any ransom you ask.

02:00:55.160 --> 02:00:58.450
Your king? Yes, of course.

02:00:58.660 --> 02:01:01.370
What will he pay me with?
Cows? Chickens?

02:01:01.540 --> 02:01:05.080
I prefer gold, and
the English have plenty.

02:01:06.340 --> 02:01:10.010
I wonder how much they'll pay
to have the witch of Orlйans.

02:01:10.220 --> 02:01:15.010
The English are arrogant, they can't
accept being defeated by a peasant girl.

02:01:15.220 --> 02:01:17.430
It has to have been the Devil's work.

02:01:17.760 --> 02:01:20.020
God defeated the English.

02:01:20.270 --> 02:01:22.730
And God who allowed you to be caught?

02:01:24.310 --> 02:01:28.400
I don't believe in God.
I don't believe in the Devil either.

02:01:28.610 --> 02:01:31.950
That's why I'm never disappointed.

02:01:33.530 --> 02:01:34.740
Sell her.

02:01:52.550 --> 02:01:53.800
To pay Jeanne's ransom.

02:01:54.050 --> 02:01:58.640
All the captains gave what they could,
as well as citizens of Orlйans.

02:01:58.850 --> 02:02:01.930
That's very generous of you.
How much?

02:02:02.180 --> 02:02:03.230
Ten thousand gold crowns.

02:02:03.770 --> 02:02:04.980
Ten thousand?

02:02:05.350 --> 02:02:06.690
That's a lot.

02:02:07.230 --> 02:02:10.820
Your Grace, I place you in charge
of this delicate negotiation.

02:02:26.080 --> 02:02:29.040
Get yourself ready. You're leaving.

02:02:32.420 --> 02:02:33.420
Who are you?

02:02:33.510 --> 02:02:35.880
Pierre Cauchon, Bishop of Beauvais.

02:02:36.630 --> 02:02:40.350
As you were captured in my diocese,
it's my duty to conduct the trial.

02:02:41.600 --> 02:02:42.890
Trial?

02:02:44.390 --> 02:02:45.390
What trial?

02:02:45.440 --> 02:02:49.020
Your trial, Jeanne,
on a charge of heresy.

02:02:52.030 --> 02:02:54.280
But my king...

02:02:55.530 --> 02:02:57.700
Didn't he pay my ransom?

02:02:57.910 --> 02:03:01.080
The English care more about you
than the French.

02:03:01.280 --> 02:03:02.540
The English?

02:03:03.370 --> 02:03:04.830
They paid your ransom.

02:03:05.330 --> 02:03:09.170
Tomorrow you'll be transferred
to their castle at Rouen.

02:04:10.850 --> 02:04:14.440
Our Christian king, Henry VI,
king of England and France...

02:04:14.650 --> 02:04:17.940
places this girl in our hands,
accused of heretical deeds...

02:04:18.190 --> 02:04:20.410
to be tried in a matter of faith.

02:04:20.990 --> 02:04:22.450
Take the Holy Gospels...

02:04:22.660 --> 02:04:26.450
and swear to tell the truth
regarding anything you may be asked.

02:04:27.870 --> 02:04:32.210
I don't know what you'll ask me. You
may ask things I won't want to answer.

02:04:32.880 --> 02:04:35.460
You will tell the truth
about everything.

02:04:35.710 --> 02:04:39.880
I will willingly tell the truth
about all earthly things.

02:04:40.090 --> 02:04:44.180
But as to my revelations,
I've told no one except my king...

02:04:45.470 --> 02:04:48.310
Charles VII, the one
and only king of France.

02:04:50.640 --> 02:04:52.810
You must take the oath.

02:04:53.020 --> 02:04:56.730
Not even a king would refuse to take
an oath in a matter of faith.

02:04:56.940 --> 02:04:59.820
I will tell you all
that I'm allowed to tell you.

02:05:00.650 --> 02:05:02.360
But as for the rest...

02:05:02.740 --> 02:05:06.330
even if you threaten to cut off
my head, I won't tell you.

02:05:11.790 --> 02:05:15.790
Begin with your name, assuming
you're allowed to tell us that much.

02:05:17.630 --> 02:05:19.170
My name is Jeanne.

02:05:20.760 --> 02:05:24.180
My little cross was taken from me.
May I have it back?

02:05:24.390 --> 02:05:27.010
Show us a little more cooperation first.

02:05:27.760 --> 02:05:29.430
Where were you born?

02:05:29.930 --> 02:05:32.440
In a village called Domrйmy.

02:05:32.640 --> 02:05:33.640
How old are you?

02:05:34.480 --> 02:05:36.770
Nineteen. Or thereabouts.

02:05:37.020 --> 02:05:38.690
Were you baptized?

02:05:40.030 --> 02:05:41.030
Yes.

02:05:41.190 --> 02:05:42.610
Recite Our Lord's Prayer.

02:05:44.660 --> 02:05:47.410
Not unless you hear my confession.

02:05:52.000 --> 02:05:54.080
Listen to me very carefully.

02:05:54.330 --> 02:05:56.500
We are all men of faith...

02:05:56.840 --> 02:06:01.300
and we shall earnestly strive for
the salvation of your body and soul.

02:06:01.510 --> 02:06:03.630
We do this in the name
of our Church...

02:06:03.840 --> 02:06:06.050
who opens her arms
to those who return to her.

02:06:06.260 --> 02:06:11.020
We cannot help you unless you submit
to our judgement and authority.

02:06:11.220 --> 02:06:13.690
Take heed of this
charitable admonition...

02:06:13.940 --> 02:06:16.400
for if you persist
in refusing our help...

02:06:16.650 --> 02:06:21.150
we shall have no choice but to
abandon you to the secular powers.

02:06:21.400 --> 02:06:24.900
I think you know the punishment
that would await you.

02:06:29.830 --> 02:06:30.990
Now...

02:06:32.080 --> 02:06:34.790
will you please recite
Our Lord's Prayer?

02:06:37.380 --> 02:06:40.090
Not unless you hear my confession.

02:06:43.670 --> 02:06:47.800
You aren't helping yourself by
refusing to submit to our judgement.

02:06:48.510 --> 02:06:51.560
You, who claim to be my judges...

02:06:51.850 --> 02:06:52.850
you be careful!

02:06:53.730 --> 02:06:55.480
For you too will be judged.

02:06:56.770 --> 02:06:58.230
Take the prisoner away!

02:07:01.400 --> 02:07:02.690
Silence!

02:07:03.780 --> 02:07:04.780
Silence!

02:07:04.860 --> 02:07:06.610
Clear the room!

02:07:07.110 --> 02:07:09.620
Clear the room! Clear the room!

02:07:11.450 --> 02:07:16.000
In future, we should conduct our
inquiries away from public pressure.

02:07:16.250 --> 02:07:19.380
Let the English burn her.
Why must it involve us?

02:07:19.580 --> 02:07:23.550
Because it's our clear duty to root
out heresy wherever we find it.

02:07:25.130 --> 02:07:26.130
Father Vincente.

02:07:27.880 --> 02:07:30.390
You're the most venerable here.
What do you think?

02:07:30.890 --> 02:07:32.970
I think this trial is a masquerade.

02:07:33.890 --> 02:07:35.600
I won't be part of it anymore.

02:07:35.850 --> 02:07:39.190
I'm willing to be her judge,
but not her executioner.

02:07:39.940 --> 02:07:41.860
That's what I'm trying to ensure.

02:07:44.530 --> 02:07:48.490
The verdict comes at the end
of a trial, Cauchon...

02:07:48.700 --> 02:07:50.030
not at the beginning.

02:07:52.160 --> 02:07:54.080
I am going back to Rome...

02:07:54.290 --> 02:07:57.210
to give my report to
our Holy Father, the Pope.

02:07:59.920 --> 02:08:03.880
This is ridiculous. Now I'm the one
who's on trial and being judged.

02:08:04.340 --> 02:08:05.630
Arrest him.

02:08:05.920 --> 02:08:07.130
What are you doing?

02:08:07.380 --> 02:08:09.720
This is an ecclesiastical court!

02:08:09.930 --> 02:08:11.970
This is English territory.

02:08:12.180 --> 02:08:14.100
I have the right to do anything.

02:08:14.350 --> 02:08:15.680
Is that clear?

02:08:32.450 --> 02:08:36.080
Our Father, who art in Heaven,
hallowed be Thy name.

02:08:36.290 --> 02:08:39.080
Give us this day our daily bread.
Forgive us our trespasses.

02:08:39.330 --> 02:08:43.170
Forgive us. Forgive and not...
Forgive us, then forgive them.

02:08:43.920 --> 02:08:46.750
Forgive them, then forgive us.
Forgive them.

02:08:46.960 --> 02:08:48.630
Why did you yell out there?

02:08:53.260 --> 02:08:56.510
What are you doing?
You can't stay here. Go away!

02:08:56.720 --> 02:08:59.520
Why? Are you waiting
for someone else?

02:09:00.890 --> 02:09:01.890
Yes.

02:09:02.480 --> 02:09:03.480
Who?

02:09:04.310 --> 02:09:05.310
My visions.

02:09:05.730 --> 02:09:07.280
Your visions?

02:09:08.400 --> 02:09:10.570
They're going to visit you in here?

02:09:10.820 --> 02:09:13.030
Yes. That's what I pray for.

02:09:13.950 --> 02:09:18.410
I want to see that. Mind if I stay
on the side? I won't bother you.

02:09:19.160 --> 02:09:22.830
No! No! You can't!
Or else they won't come.

02:09:23.040 --> 02:09:26.000
- Why won't they?
- Because I have to be alone.

02:09:26.460 --> 02:09:29.760
They won't come anyway.

02:09:30.630 --> 02:09:32.220
What do you mean?

02:09:32.430 --> 02:09:33.510
Why would they?

02:09:34.840 --> 02:09:39.720
Because I've been faithful to God, and
I've followed everything He's said.

02:09:39.970 --> 02:09:43.770
- I've done everything He's ever asked.
- God asked you to do something?

02:09:48.270 --> 02:09:49.940
Yes. Lots of things.

02:09:50.190 --> 02:09:54.910
You mean God said,
"I need you, Jeanne"?

02:09:56.570 --> 02:09:57.660
No.

02:09:57.870 --> 02:10:00.700
But He sent me signs.

02:10:02.540 --> 02:10:05.040
Signs. What signs?

02:10:07.340 --> 02:10:08.960
The wind. The wind.

02:10:13.510 --> 02:10:14.510
Wind?

02:10:14.880 --> 02:10:17.390
And the clouds. Ringing.

02:10:20.560 --> 02:10:21.810
Ringing cloud?

02:10:22.770 --> 02:10:25.400
The dance. The dance.

02:10:28.610 --> 02:10:29.980
The dance.

02:10:30.980 --> 02:10:31.980
The dance.

02:10:34.110 --> 02:10:35.110
The dance.

02:10:39.410 --> 02:10:40.410
The sword.

02:10:40.620 --> 02:10:44.080
The sword lying in the field.
That was a sign.

02:10:44.290 --> 02:10:47.580
No, that was a sword in a field.

02:10:49.960 --> 02:10:51.630
No. That was a sign.

02:10:51.840 --> 02:10:54.630
No. That was a sword in a field.

02:10:54.840 --> 02:10:57.300
It can't just get there by itself.

02:10:58.220 --> 02:11:01.850
It can't. A sword just
doesn't get there by itself.

02:11:02.060 --> 02:11:06.140
True. Every event has an infinite
number of causes, so why pick one?

02:11:06.350 --> 02:11:09.190
There are many ways a sword
might get to a field.

02:11:14.690 --> 02:11:18.160
Seems a perfectly valid explanation,
but how about this one?

02:11:24.370 --> 02:11:26.210
There are other possibilities.

02:11:31.170 --> 02:11:32.210
Or even faster.

02:11:35.920 --> 02:11:38.800
And that's without counting
the inexplicable.

02:11:41.300 --> 02:11:45.390
From an infinite number of
possibilities, you had to pick this.

02:11:59.280 --> 02:12:02.450
You didn't see what was, Jeanne.

02:12:03.200 --> 02:12:06.200
You saw what you wanted to see.

02:12:22.470 --> 02:12:26.390
This voice that you say
appears to you...

02:12:26.640 --> 02:12:30.400
is it an angel or a saint,
or does it come from God?

02:12:31.150 --> 02:12:34.900
I won't tell you any more about that.
I'm more afraid...

02:12:35.150 --> 02:12:37.490
of displeasing Him
than not answering you.

02:12:38.240 --> 02:12:41.360
You're afraid of displeasing God
by telling the truth?

02:12:41.570 --> 02:12:42.570
No.

02:12:42.660 --> 02:12:44.830
Did God forbid you
to tell the truth?

02:12:45.030 --> 02:12:46.030
No.

02:12:46.080 --> 02:12:49.870
My revelations were for
the king of France, not for you.

02:12:51.960 --> 02:12:56.840
When you first saw your king,
was there an angel over his head?

02:12:57.050 --> 02:12:58.800
If there was, I did not see it.

02:12:59.010 --> 02:13:01.840
Why did your king believe in you
without any proof?

02:13:03.050 --> 02:13:04.430
Go and ask him yourself.

02:13:18.940 --> 02:13:20.360
Dinner.

02:13:35.670 --> 02:13:38.880
When you were taken prisoner,
did you have a horse?

02:13:39.300 --> 02:13:42.380
Yes. A half-steed. Black.

02:13:42.590 --> 02:13:45.010
- And who gave you that horse?
- My king.

02:13:45.220 --> 02:13:46.470
How many did he give you?

02:13:49.850 --> 02:13:54.810
Five steeds and a few hackneys.

02:13:55.060 --> 02:13:58.270
As much as for a lord.
What an honour.

02:13:58.480 --> 02:14:01.690
Did he give you other wealth
apart from those horses?

02:14:01.900 --> 02:14:02.900
No.

02:14:03.400 --> 02:14:07.700
What about all those dresses you were
given? Silk dresses, weren't they?

02:14:09.120 --> 02:14:12.080
Yes. Yes, I was given a few.

02:14:13.000 --> 02:14:16.500
But I never had time to wear them.

02:14:16.710 --> 02:14:20.090
Still, pretty wealthy for a peasant
girl, wouldn't you say?

02:14:22.670 --> 02:14:26.640
You look pretty wealthy for a servant
of God, wouldn't you say?

02:14:32.270 --> 02:14:34.980
You launched an attack on Paris,
didn't you?

02:14:35.190 --> 02:14:36.350
I tried to.

02:14:36.560 --> 02:14:40.020
You ordered Paris to surrender
in the name of the King of Heaven?

02:14:40.860 --> 02:14:44.280
No, I said, "Surrender in the name
of the king of France."

02:14:44.490 --> 02:14:47.320
That is not what is written
in the evidence.

02:14:48.660 --> 02:14:50.030
Look for yourself.

02:14:52.500 --> 02:14:53.500
I can't read.

02:14:55.120 --> 02:14:56.920
Yes, I forgot.

02:14:57.630 --> 02:15:01.670
God sent us an illiterate peasant
to carry out an important mission.

02:15:01.880 --> 02:15:04.260
Do you think God
made the right decision?

02:15:04.470 --> 02:15:08.010
To take an ignorant girl to save
the kingdom of France?

02:15:08.850 --> 02:15:10.430
I leave that answer to God.

02:15:15.140 --> 02:15:16.310
Fuck!

02:15:16.810 --> 02:15:18.440
Calm down, I beg you.

02:15:18.690 --> 02:15:21.820
How can I, when I'm the
laughingstock of the court?

02:15:22.030 --> 02:15:26.280
This girl has a way with people,
but we're making progress every day.

02:15:26.490 --> 02:15:30.240
As long as she's alive, our armies
refuse to fight. Understand?

02:15:30.450 --> 02:15:32.290
They need proof God's on their side!

02:15:32.490 --> 02:15:35.250
It's not for us to burn her.
That's your prerogative.

02:15:35.460 --> 02:15:37.120
You must find her guilty!

02:15:37.330 --> 02:15:40.460
We can't do that unless
she admits to blasphemy.

02:15:40.670 --> 02:15:42.170
What are you waiting for?

02:15:42.380 --> 02:15:45.420
You've got a castle full of racks!
Torture her!

02:15:45.630 --> 02:15:48.430
You'll never get anything
out of her that way.

02:15:48.640 --> 02:15:50.970
And besides...

02:15:51.300 --> 02:15:56.430
you must realize that several
of my colleagues are scared.

02:15:57.310 --> 02:15:59.310
Scared? Of a girl?

02:15:59.520 --> 02:16:01.560
Scared to make a mistake.

02:16:02.230 --> 02:16:04.070
Suppose she's right.

02:16:04.440 --> 02:16:06.860
Suppose she has been sent by God.

02:16:11.370 --> 02:16:12.660
Whose side are you on?

02:16:13.080 --> 02:16:15.950
I'm on the side
of Holy Mother Church.

02:16:17.080 --> 02:16:18.210
You have a sword?

02:16:20.420 --> 02:16:21.420
Quite a few.

02:16:21.580 --> 02:16:23.880
Didn't you also carry a banner?

02:16:24.590 --> 02:16:25.590
Yes.

02:16:25.630 --> 02:16:28.720
Which do you prefer?
Your banner or your sword?

02:16:28.970 --> 02:16:31.300
I was 40 times more fond of my banner.

02:16:31.510 --> 02:16:34.309
Why? Did it have some
particular value or power?

02:16:35.639 --> 02:16:36.680
No.

02:16:39.389 --> 02:16:41.059
It's just, a sword is a weapon.

02:16:41.270 --> 02:16:42.270
And?

02:16:44.730 --> 02:16:47.440
And so I prefer my banner.

02:16:47.690 --> 02:16:48.690
Why?

02:16:49.360 --> 02:16:51.660
To avoid killing anyone.

02:16:51.870 --> 02:16:56.450
So if you'd not been carrying your
banner, you'd have killed more people?

02:17:00.040 --> 02:17:02.750
No. Of course not.
I never killed anyone.

02:17:02.920 --> 02:17:07.629
Then perhaps the temptation to kill
would have been stronger...

02:17:07.840 --> 02:17:10.180
too strong perhaps.

02:17:10.469 --> 02:17:13.090
No. I warned the English
to go back home.

02:17:13.299 --> 02:17:15.850
I begged them not to force us to fight.

02:17:16.059 --> 02:17:20.520
We have witnesses who can confirm you
were not always carrying your banner.

02:17:24.809 --> 02:17:26.400
Yes, perhaps.

02:17:26.610 --> 02:17:28.740
Sometimes you carried
just your sword?

02:17:30.490 --> 02:17:32.320
Yes. I don't know.

02:17:32.660 --> 02:17:34.280
Did you use the sword?

02:17:34.530 --> 02:17:36.740
Yes, I used it to...
I held it up...

02:17:36.950 --> 02:17:40.209
You held up your sword
and flourished it about like this!

02:17:40.459 --> 02:17:41.459
I don't remember.

02:17:41.540 --> 02:17:44.379
You were in the battlefield
with your sword...

02:17:44.629 --> 02:17:46.000
waving it about...

02:17:46.209 --> 02:17:48.510
charging against
the enemy, screaming...

02:17:48.709 --> 02:17:50.010
fighting for life...

02:17:50.260 --> 02:17:54.260
and you expect us to believe
that in all this excitement...

02:17:55.680 --> 02:17:59.809
you never killed anyone?

02:18:00.520 --> 02:18:03.350
No. I never killed anyone.

02:18:05.610 --> 02:18:07.070
I can't believe you can lie.

02:18:07.270 --> 02:18:08.270
I'm not lying.

02:18:08.480 --> 02:18:10.400
Leave me alone!
I can't remember.

02:18:10.610 --> 02:18:12.320
I never killed anyone.

02:18:12.570 --> 02:18:14.240
Let me help your memory.

02:18:14.450 --> 02:18:17.080
I don't want to hear!
I didn't kill that man!

02:18:17.280 --> 02:18:18.580
Leave me alone!

02:18:19.040 --> 02:18:21.540
Stop. Stop. I can't remember.

02:18:21.750 --> 02:18:25.879
The battles were confusing! I was only
defending myself as best as I could.

02:18:26.129 --> 02:18:29.959
There was dust and smoke and noise.
I was being attacked on all sides.

02:18:30.170 --> 02:18:34.840
So maybe, perhaps, I fought back.
But it was only to defend myself.

02:18:35.049 --> 02:18:36.760
So your memory's coming back?

02:18:36.969 --> 02:18:37.969
- Yes.
- Good.

02:18:38.010 --> 02:18:42.270
Now, tell me why God let all those
battles happen in the first place.

02:18:42.480 --> 02:18:46.150
He's so powerful.
He's the creator of Heaven and Earth.

02:18:46.400 --> 02:18:49.610
He could easily have stopped
all that blood and misery.

02:18:49.820 --> 02:18:50.820
Why didn't He...

02:18:50.860 --> 02:18:53.570
Is He the one who spread
blood and misery?

02:18:53.780 --> 02:18:56.490
- Is He?
- But He could have stopped it.

02:18:56.910 --> 02:18:58.660
What did He get? Pleasure?

02:18:58.910 --> 02:19:02.410
Pleasure from watching us killing
each other in His name?

02:19:02.620 --> 02:19:05.959
- In His name?
- Yes. In His name.

02:19:06.209 --> 02:19:09.590
We fought and killed in His name,
the King of Heaven!

02:19:09.790 --> 02:19:10.790
Really?

02:19:10.840 --> 02:19:13.340
Let all those who love me, follow me!

02:19:13.549 --> 02:19:18.680
"Let all who love me, follow me!"
Where does God get mentioned?

02:19:18.889 --> 02:19:20.969
Come on, Jeanne.

02:19:21.180 --> 02:19:22.809
Be honest.

02:19:23.100 --> 02:19:25.940
You fought for yourself. In your name.

02:19:27.980 --> 02:19:30.360
I was defending myself
as best as I could.

02:19:30.610 --> 02:19:33.400
Everyone has the right to defend
themselves, don't they?

02:19:33.610 --> 02:19:36.530
They do! Should I have
let myself get killed?

02:19:36.740 --> 02:19:39.490
No. You did fine.
I'd even say well done.

02:19:39.700 --> 02:19:44.830
In fact, the ones you killed
probably deserved it, don't you think?

02:19:45.410 --> 02:19:46.580
No!

02:19:46.790 --> 02:19:47.790
No.

02:19:48.540 --> 02:19:51.420
I never thought killing
would bring about peace.

02:19:51.630 --> 02:19:52.630
I agree.

02:19:52.670 --> 02:19:54.960
Peace will only be got
at the end of a lance.

02:19:55.170 --> 02:19:58.130
I don't agree. Why do you
keep changing your mind?

02:20:00.010 --> 02:20:01.010
You.

02:20:03.060 --> 02:20:04.720
Why are you doing this to me?

02:20:04.970 --> 02:20:06.980
You get pleasure from hurting me?

02:20:08.310 --> 02:20:10.940
Pleasure. That's a difficult
word to define.

02:20:12.320 --> 02:20:15.240
When does the pain end
and the pleasure begin?

02:20:15.440 --> 02:20:18.950
When did your pleasure begin,
with that...

02:20:19.200 --> 02:20:20.870
sword in your hand?

02:20:22.490 --> 02:20:25.200
I never took pleasure...

02:20:25.660 --> 02:20:28.210
in hurting anyone.

02:20:29.420 --> 02:20:30.750
Really?

02:20:56.110 --> 02:20:59.400
Set me free. Set me free.

02:20:59.820 --> 02:21:01.360
You will be, Jeanne.

02:21:02.490 --> 02:21:04.160
You will be.

02:21:25.640 --> 02:21:28.140
Jeanne, my very dear friend
in Christ...

02:21:28.350 --> 02:21:32.770
we, your judges, desirous of
reaching a true and lawful verdict...

02:21:33.020 --> 02:21:37.610
submitted a transcript of your trial
to the University of Paris.

02:21:38.190 --> 02:21:42.530
After careful consideration,
the scholars have concluded with us...

02:21:42.740 --> 02:21:45.620
that you have committed
many grievous sins.

02:21:46.280 --> 02:21:49.410
I ask you to listen carefully
to their opinion...

02:21:49.660 --> 02:21:51.540
as detailed in these articles.

02:21:55.000 --> 02:21:56.090
"Article 1:

02:21:56.340 --> 02:22:00.300
You said that by God's command you have
continually worn men's clothes...

02:22:00.510 --> 02:22:02.550
and you have also
worn your hair short...

02:22:02.760 --> 02:22:05.930
with nothing to distinguish you
from the soldiers.

02:22:06.680 --> 02:22:09.430
As to this article,
the scholars have declared..."

02:22:09.640 --> 02:22:12.350
Don't abandon me. Please.

02:22:14.520 --> 02:22:16.110
Where are You?

02:22:17.650 --> 02:22:19.940
Where are You? Please.

02:22:23.700 --> 02:22:27.740
Is this what You want?
Is this what You want?

02:22:28.240 --> 02:22:29.990
Do You want me to...

02:22:31.000 --> 02:22:32.410
to burn...

02:22:33.500 --> 02:22:35.170
without...

02:22:35.500 --> 02:22:37.380
being confessed?

02:22:38.340 --> 02:22:41.170
Finally, article 12.

02:22:41.380 --> 02:22:43.630
"You have said you won't
submit yourself...

02:22:43.840 --> 02:22:47.180
to the judgement of the church
militant, but only to God."

02:22:47.390 --> 02:22:50.270
The scholars say that you
have no comprehension...

02:22:50.470 --> 02:22:52.310
of the Church's authority...

02:22:52.520 --> 02:22:55.310
that you've perniciously erred
in the faith of God...

02:22:55.560 --> 02:23:00.320
that you're a child of superstition,
a wanderer from the faith...

02:23:00.940 --> 02:23:04.610
an invoker of demons,
an idolater and a heretic.

02:23:15.750 --> 02:23:19.130
We once again admonish,
beg and exalt you...

02:23:19.380 --> 02:23:22.840
to cast out and recant
your erroneous beliefs...

02:23:23.090 --> 02:23:26.180
by signing this recantation.

02:23:27.220 --> 02:23:28.220
Please.

02:23:29.890 --> 02:23:31.390
If the Church...

02:23:32.020 --> 02:23:34.600
wants me to say...

02:23:35.230 --> 02:23:37.440
that my visions are evil...

02:23:37.850 --> 02:23:40.650
then I do not believe
in this Church.

02:23:46.070 --> 02:23:47.780
Perform your office!

02:23:53.290 --> 02:23:54.290
Wait.

02:23:58.960 --> 02:24:01.540
Jeanne, I beg of you, sign.

02:24:02.090 --> 02:24:05.170
Don't you understand?
I'm trying to save you.

02:24:05.380 --> 02:24:07.590
I want to be confessed.

02:24:08.720 --> 02:24:11.350
Sign this and I will
confess you myself.

02:24:16.230 --> 02:24:19.060
And may I go to Mass?

02:24:19.270 --> 02:24:21.110
As often as you like.

02:24:21.310 --> 02:24:24.030
Now, for the love of God, sign.

02:24:29.320 --> 02:24:32.530
Sign, Jeanne, and you'll be
free of your chains.

02:24:32.780 --> 02:24:33.950
Free of the fire.

02:25:10.450 --> 02:25:11.660
Thank you.

02:25:15.370 --> 02:25:17.500
You know what you just signed?

02:25:18.620 --> 02:25:21.040
You just signed away His existence.

02:25:22.580 --> 02:25:23.630
I didn't mean to.

02:25:23.840 --> 02:25:25.460
For you...

02:25:25.840 --> 02:25:27.340
He's a lie.

02:25:28.760 --> 02:25:30.380
An illusion.

02:25:30.970 --> 02:25:35.260
No, no. He told me
that I would be confessed.

02:25:36.180 --> 02:25:39.270
In the end it was you
who abandoned Him.

02:25:44.940 --> 02:25:47.650
May I have that back, please?

02:25:47.820 --> 02:25:49.900
You have nothing to regret.

02:25:50.110 --> 02:25:51.110
No.

02:25:51.360 --> 02:25:52.410
Give it back to me!

02:25:52.610 --> 02:25:53.780
Give it back!

02:25:55.490 --> 02:25:57.080
Take her away!

02:26:01.920 --> 02:26:03.290
Silence her!

02:26:08.210 --> 02:26:09.210
There.

02:26:09.300 --> 02:26:10.470
She has recanted.

02:26:10.670 --> 02:26:12.760
And we accept her repentance...

02:26:12.970 --> 02:26:16.430
for the Church never closes
her arms to those who return to it.

02:26:18.310 --> 02:26:22.390
Now she's your martyr, not ours.

02:26:48.750 --> 02:26:50.510
Please! Please!

02:26:56.890 --> 02:26:57.890
Enough.

02:27:05.560 --> 02:27:06.560
Here.

02:27:07.690 --> 02:27:11.360
If you want to get dressed,
try these for size.

02:27:17.740 --> 02:27:19.160
My lord bishop!

02:27:29.960 --> 02:27:31.710
Come to see for yourself.

02:27:31.960 --> 02:27:33.720
Well, take a look.

02:27:39.350 --> 02:27:41.510
You see? Dressed as a man again.

02:27:42.060 --> 02:27:44.770
Her repentance didn't
last very long, did it?

02:27:45.640 --> 02:27:50.440
The Bishop of Senlis was passing by and
was on hand to witness her relapse.

02:27:52.900 --> 02:27:55.990
And by what miracle did these
clothes get here?

02:27:56.200 --> 02:28:00.370
Not a miracle, my dear Cauchon.
An evil spell.

02:28:00.580 --> 02:28:04.660
This girl is a witch, and tomorrow
she will burn for it.

02:28:05.910 --> 02:28:08.540
Have the stake prepared
in the marketplace.

02:28:24.270 --> 02:28:26.390
Jeanne, I don't understand.

02:28:26.640 --> 02:28:28.140
Why did you do it?

02:28:28.440 --> 02:28:29.440
And you.

02:28:29.690 --> 02:28:31.060
Why did you lie?

02:28:31.770 --> 02:28:33.320
You promised I'd be confessed.

02:28:33.530 --> 02:28:36.530
It was the only way to have you
saved from the fire.

02:28:36.990 --> 02:28:39.990
It's not my body I want to save.

02:28:40.200 --> 02:28:41.660
It's my soul.

02:28:43.450 --> 02:28:45.160
I ask only one thing:

02:28:46.290 --> 02:28:47.460
Please...

02:28:48.330 --> 02:28:49.830
hear my confession.

02:28:53.630 --> 02:28:55.340
I can't, Jeanne.

02:28:56.130 --> 02:28:58.170
I can't hear your confession.

02:29:00.760 --> 02:29:02.180
I'm very sorry.

02:29:23.700 --> 02:29:25.330
You want to confess?

02:29:29.540 --> 02:29:31.000
I'm listening.

02:29:32.210 --> 02:29:34.420
I've committed sins, my Lord.

02:29:37.630 --> 02:29:39.380
So many sins.

02:29:43.010 --> 02:29:44.260
I saw...

02:29:44.970 --> 02:29:46.810
so many signs.

02:29:47.020 --> 02:29:48.980
Many signs.

02:29:50.980 --> 02:29:53.190
The ones I wanted to see.

02:29:59.070 --> 02:30:01.860
I fought...

02:30:04.740 --> 02:30:06.450
out of revenge...

02:30:09.700 --> 02:30:11.210
and despair.

02:30:18.670 --> 02:30:20.380
I was all the things...

02:30:21.670 --> 02:30:23.680
that people believe...

02:30:25.640 --> 02:30:27.640
they are allowed to be...

02:30:29.220 --> 02:30:31.020
when they're fighting for...

02:30:35.020 --> 02:30:36.190
a cause.

02:30:37.440 --> 02:30:38.610
For a cause.

02:30:40.990 --> 02:30:42.240
I was...

